{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584195"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:41:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:41:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14429"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14429","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14429"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.61,0.05,0,0,0.34]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7124"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115553"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7124","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7124"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14429"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97556"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4906"},{"type":"tags","id":"4907"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6641"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17021"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17161"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115553","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115553"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements is correct regarding subacute infective endocarditis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Most commonly caused by Streptococcus viridans","Typically results in rapid valve destruction","Most commonly requires surgical management","Occurs predominantly on normal heart valves","Intravenous drug use is a significant risk factor"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESubacute infective endocarditis is \u003Cstrong\u003Emost commonly caused by \u003Cem\u003EStreptococcus viridans\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E, a group of oral commensal bacteria. This is in contrast to acute infective endocarditis, which is most often caused by \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESubacute infective endocarditis does not \u003Cstrong\u003Etypically result in rapid valve destruction\u003C/strong\u003E. Instead, it has a more gradual onset and progression over weeks to months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile some cases may require surgical intervention, it is not correct that subacute infective endocarditis \u003Cstrong\u003Emost commonly requires surgical management\u003C/strong\u003E. Many cases can be treated with appropriate antibiotic therapy alone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESubacute infective endocarditis does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccur predominantly on normal heart valves\u003C/strong\u003E. In fact, it most often affects previously damaged or abnormal valves, such as those affected by rheumatic heart disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eintravenous drug use is a significant risk factor\u003C/strong\u003E for infective endocarditis, it is more commonly associated with acute rather than subacute infective endocarditis. Subacute infective endocarditis is more often associated with pre-existing valvular disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Subacute infective endocarditis is most commonly caused by Streptococcus viridans.","Rheumatic heart disease is a significant risk factor for subacute infective endocarditis.","Subacute infective endocarditis typically occurs on previously damaged heart valves."],"references":["Colvin, R. B., Chang, A., Farris, A. B., Kambham, N., Cornell, L. D., Meehan, S. M., ... \u0026 L